# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# DATA class (see .dataclass.json) — real-run output. It lives in the private companion config
# (~/.shopping-aggregator-config/data/, resolved by tools/datadir.py) and is PHYSICALLY ABSENT from
# this repo. The repo ships only the `.example` schema, so a fresh clone is a usable, uninitialized
# tool with nothing real inside it to copy.
#
# live-runs.jsonl is why this section exists. It is append-only telemetry of REAL runs — one line per
# source touched — so it accumulated which products were priced, which retailers were bought from and
# which region they ship to. Every content scan passed it: there is no email or phone in a domain
# slug. The leak was never a bad regex, it was a pipe pointing at a public repo.
skills/shopping-aggregator/metrics/live-runs.jsonl
skills/shopping-aggregator/metrics/gh-api-cache.json
!skills/shopping-aggregator/metrics/*.example
